iaries, what are they? Hasn't Reid merely swapped the common ‘sensation’ for the notorious ‘idea’, ending up with indirect realism? 1 Current imaginative strategies answer negatively: Reid's sensory sign does not contradict direct perception, and those who think otherwise merely fail to understand what it means.","topics":["metaphysics","mind"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0378.2007.00282.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0378.2008.00336.x","title":"Naturalism, Method and Genealogy in Beyond Selflessness","authors":["P. J. E. Kail"],"journal":"ejp","published":"2009-02-19","volume":"17","issue":"1","pages":"113-120","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0378.2008.00336.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0378.2007.00277.x","title":"Merleau‐Ponty's Account of Hallucination","authors":["Komarine Romdenh‐Romluc"],"journal":"ejp","published":"2009-02-19","volume":"17","issue":"1","pages":"76-90","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0378.2007.00277.x"}]